{
  "text": "To achieve the stated runtime, it suffices to show that \u2225A i \u2225/\u2225D i \u2225 is constant for a constant fraction of users in S. We sketch the proof here; the details are in Kerenidis and Prakash's proof [CITATION_1] . We know that \u2225T \u2212 D \u2225 F \u2264 O(\u03c1 + \u03b5)\u2225T \u2225 F . Through counting arguments we can show that, for a (1 \u2212 \u03c8 \u2032 )-fraction of typical users S \u2032\u2032 \u2282 S,",
